n of prevention and wellness promotion, along with multicultural and feminist theories. Throughout this book, five case studies, which are introduced in Chapter One, are revisited to help the readers make important and meaningful connections between theory and practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aChild abusezUnited StatesxPrevention. 0aChild abusezUnited States. 0aChild welfarezUnited States. 0aMulticulturalismzUnited States. 7aFAMILY & RELATIONSHIPS / General.2bisacsh  achild abuse prevention, child abuse cases, child neglect, child maltreatment, alaskan natives, alaskan native families, alaskan natives family values, marginalized communities, feminist perspectives, feminism, social activism, ethnic communities, family dynamics, generational trauma, multicultural theories, resources for social workers, resources for general practitioners, intervention in child maltreatment, child abuse survival stories, child abuse case studies, black communities, hispanic communities in the US, black communities in the US.1 aDeBoard-Lucas, Renee L., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aSinger, Rachel R., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2022 Englishz978311099395008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2022z9783110994186oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076647940uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9781978822610?locatt=mode:legacy40u